to follow up the other person's advice about:

    apt-get update

That's needed for the very first installation.
After that (provided that you have both enabled APT lists and APT packages in Persistence settings), you don't need to update every single time because lists + package are cached.
Installing a newer version of your package requires 'apt-get update' again, of course.
